{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets strict POSIX mode."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/optioncontext\/set(strictposix:)"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"strictPosix"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, this mode is disabled."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In strict POSIX mode, the first non-argument parameter encountered"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(eg: filename) terminates argument processing.  Remaining arguments"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"are treated as non-options and are not attempted to be parsed.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If strict POSIX mode is disabled then parsing is done in the GNU way","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"where option arguments can be freely mixed with non-options.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As an example, consider “ls foo -l”.  With GNU style parsing, this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"will list “foo” in long mode.  In strict POSIX style, this will list"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the files named “foo” and “-l”.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It may be useful to force strict POSIX mode when creating “verb"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"style” command line tools.  For example, the “gsettings” command line"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"tool supports the global option “–schemadir” as well as many"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"subcommands (“get”, “set”, etc.) which each have their own set of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"arguments.  Using strict POSIX mode will allow parsing the global"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"options up to the verb name while leaving the remaining options to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"parsed by the relevant subcommand (which can be determined by","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"examining the verb name, which should be present in argv[1] after","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"parsing)."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContext","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContext\/OptionContextProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"set(strictPosix:)","role":"symbol","extendedModule":"GLib","externalID":"s:4GLib21OptionContextProtocolPAAE3set11strictPosixySb_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib13OptionContextC","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"strictPosix","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}]},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContext\/set(strictPosix:)"},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/OptionContext/set(strictPosix:)":{"role":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/optioncontext\/set(strictposix:)","abstract":[{"text":"Sets strict POSIX mode.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"strictPosix"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContext\/set(strictPosix:)","kind":"symbol","title":"set(strictPosix:)"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/OptionContext/OptionContextProtocol-Implementations":{"title":"OptionContextProtocol Implementations","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/optioncontext\/optioncontextprotocol-implementations","abstract":[],"role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContext\/OptionContextProtocol-Implementations","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/OptionContext":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OptionContext","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/optioncontext","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GOptionContext"},{"type":"text","text":" struct defines which options"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"are accepted by the commandline option parser. The struct has only private","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fields and should not be directly accessed.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"OptionContext","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContext","kind":"symbol","title":"OptionContext"}}}